20/12/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Six people became victims of bad weather in south and western Turkey on Saturday (December 19th). 
In the western province of Balikesir strong winds blew away a minaret in a local village, killing four people and injuring two others. 
In the town of Menemen in the Izmir province, a man was killed when he was hit by falling debris caused by a mini tornado. 
Another man died when a wall collapsed due to torrential rains in the city of Antakya in the Hatay province. 
Electricity and water have been shut off due to flooding. 
(Anadolu news agency, AFP - 19/12/09)
